'''Toufen''' ([[Hakka Chinese|Hakka]] [[Pha̍k-fa-sṳ|PFS]]: ''Thèu-fun''; [[Hokkien]] [[Pe̍h-ōe-jī|POJ]]: ''Thâu-hūn'') is a [[Townships and county-administered cities|county-administered city]] in northern [[Miaoli County]], [[Taiwan]]. Its city centre forms a continuous urban area with [[Zhunan]].
==History== In 2007, there was a revitalization project for the community houses in the city which was funded by [[Council of Cultural Affairs]] and private sectors which turned the buildings into a museum of chronicling life in the 1950s and 1960s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2015/10/17/2003630276|date=17 October 2015|title=Renovated cluster of Miaoli houses bring tourists, jobs|publisher=Taipei Times|accessdate=11 May 2017}}</ref> On 5 October 2015, Toufen was upgraded from an [[Township (Taiwan)|urban township]] to a county-controlled city.<ref>{{cite|url=http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/politics/breakingnews/1381240|publisher=[[Liberty Times]]|author=鄭鴻達|date=2015-07-16|script-title=zh:苗栗頭份改制縣轄市 鎮代表會落槌通過|language=Chinese}}</ref>
==Geography== Toufen has an area of {{convert|53.3029|km2|abbr=on}}. Surrounding the city are Miaoli County's [[Zhunan, Miaoli|Zhunan]], [[Zaoqiao]] and [[Sanwan, Miaoli|Sanwan]] townships to the northwest/west, southwest and southeast, respectively, and [[Hsinchu County]] to the northeast and east.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.toufen.gov.tw/toufen/1-2.php | script-title =zh:地理環境 | trans-title =Geography & environment | language =Chinese | website =toufen.gov.tw | publisher =Toufen City Office | access-date =6 February 2017 | quote = }}</ref> As of January 2017, its total population was estimated at 103,162, including 52,055 males and 51,107 females.<ref name=pop>{{cite web | url =http://mlhr.miaoli.gov.tw/xlsgetfile_10601m.php | script-title =zh:106年一月份人口統計下載區 | trans-title=January 2017 Population Statistic Downloads | language=Chinese | date =January 2017 | website =mlhr.miaoli.gov.tw | publisher =Miaoli County Government Household Registration Service | access-date =25 February 2017}}</ref>
==Administrative divisions== The city comprises 32 villages: Chenggong, Douhuan, Gexing, Guangxing, Heping, Houzhuang, Jianguo, Jianshan, Jianxia, Lankeng, Liutung, Luzhu, Minquan, Minsheng, Minzu, Pantao, Renai, Shangpu, Shangxing, Shanhu, Shanxia, Tianliao, Tongzhuang, Toufen, Tuniu, Wenhua, Xiaxing, Xinglong, Xinhua, Xinyi, Zhongxiao and Zijiang.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.toufen.gov.tw/toufen/1-7.php | script-title =zh:行政區域 | trans-title =Administrative areas | language =Chinese | website =toufen.gov.tw | publisher =Toufen City Office | access-date =6 February 2017 | quote = }}</ref>
